title: Dean Smith opens Walsall contract talks
text:
Tweet The League One leaders have held early discussions with the popular manager whose contract expires at the end of the season.
Walsall rejected an approach for Smith from Rotherham last week and he confirmed he has entered talks to extend his deal. 
"We've had preliminary talks and they'll be on-going," he said. 
"I'm happy here and enjoy it and hopefully we can sort something out soon. 
"I know people laugh but I've always called us getting to the Championship the 'improbable dream' - the impossible dream is getting to the Premier League. More on this story:
